Rift Valley fever, South Africa
-------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 16 May 2018 from Dr Bothle Michael Modisane, Chief Director , Department of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Animal Production and Health, Pretoria, South Africa

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 28 Apr 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 16 May 2018
Report date: 16 May 2018
Date submitted to OIE: 16 May 2018
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 30 Aug 2011
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Rift Valley fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1 (RVF_2018_001): Letsemeng, Free State
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Apr 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 600 / 250 / 250 / 0 / 0
Affected population: cattle, sheep, goats, and camels sera samples for active surveillance at the livestock border market.

